olive oil
1 head Cos Lettuce
1 stalk Celery
1 Apple
1 packet flaked almonds
2 packet beef strips
1 sachet Herb & Mushroom Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Roughly chop cos lettuce. Thinly slice celery. Thinly slice apple into sticks.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast flaked almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes. Set aside.
• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging.
• In a bowl, combine beef strips, Aussie spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil.

• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add half the honey and toss to coat.
TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• In a large bowl, combine Dijon mustard, mayonnaise, the remaining honey and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Add cos, celery and apple to the dressing and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide apple cos salad between bowls.
• Top with herbed beef and sprinkle over flaked almonds. Enjoy!